 by elite men into that mass-produced commodity used in classrooms worldwide-the humble school globe. Traversing the length and breadth of British India, Terrestrial Lessons is an unconventional history of this master object of pedagogical modernity that will fascinate historians of cartography, science, and Asian studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aGeographyxStudy and teachingzIndiaxHistory. 0aGlobeszIndiaxHistory. 4aIndia. 4acolonial pedagogy. 4aschool globe. 4aterrestrial globe. 4aterrestrial lessons. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226476742423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226476742.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles